definition.value: A Region of the Republic of the Congo in the western part of the country. It borders the departments of Bouenza, Kouilou, and Lekoumou, and internationally, Gabon, the Democratic Republic of the Congo, and the Cabinda portion of Angola. The regional capital is Dolisie.
Not DRC, but Republic of Congo.
A populated place. A town located in Ogooue-Ivindo province, Gabon.
A populated place. A small village in on the banks of the Zadie River.
Also: Many other Mbomo in Gabon.
A Region of the Republic of the Congo in the western part of the country. It borders the departments of Cuvette and Sangha, and Gabon. The capital is Ewo.
Also: Several populated places with this name in Republic of Congo.
A populated place. The main city of Batna Province, Algeria. Batna is located in the north east of Algeria, not far from Constantine and the Tunisian border.
The fourth largest city in Morocco.
A populated place. A city in western Morocco, located on the Atlantic Ocean. It is the capital of the Greater Casablanca region.
The capital of the mid-southwestern Moroccan economic region of Marrakech-Tensift-Al Haouz, near the foothills of the Atlas Mountains.
An unincorporated census-designated place located in western Fairfax County, Virginia in the Washington, DC metropolitan area.
A province of Angola. Uige is the capital of the province.
A province of Angola. Luanda is the capital of the province and the country.

A province of Mozambique; the province excludes the city of Maputo (which comprises a separate province). Faz limite, a norte com a provincia de Gaza, a leste com o Oceano Indico, a sul com provincia sul-africana do KwaZulu-Natal e a oeste com a Suazilandia e com a provincia sul-africana de Mpumalanga.
The third most populous city in South Africa, forming part of the eThekwini metropolitan municipality.
A small town situated in North West Province of South Africa.
A city that is the capital and largest city of Zambia. It is located in the southern part of the central plateau of the country, at an elevation of 1300 m.
The capital of Western Province in Zambia.
A populated place. A city in Zimbabwe in the Mashonaland West province, 140km south-west of Harare on the main road to Bulawayo.
The second largest city in Zimbabwe.
A city, commercial centre and river port on the eastern bank of the Niger river in Anambra State, southeast Nigeria.
A region located in Imo State, southeastern Nigeria. Set in the heart of Igboland, it is gradually developing into towns and cities.
